      },
      "date": "2014-06-24 14:22:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDidn't know that this patch existed.  Do you have a master version?  If so where is it.  Ryan Haasken has a similar patch (for master) at http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10257/3 and LU-5026.  It adds a separate trigger, so I expect that it would be preferred.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a628269daf02a603333f049688bcae628a26ffb0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 373,
        "name": "Ryan Haasken",
        "email": "haasken@cray.com",
        "username": "rhaasken"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 14:27:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCory, this change does say \"master\" for the Branch.\n\nI do have a similar patch that adds the proc interface lbug_on_eviction.  I think it is more clear to have a separate, properly named interface (as my patch does) to enable this behavior.  However, this patch does have the benefit that no extra, unused proc file will exist on the server.  The behavior of dump_on_eviction would have to be properly documented in the Lustre manual.  Which approach is preferred?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1a359eb7f86d98ebf13654bc0cbca173dca17bcd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 6,
        "name": "Cory Spitz",
