          "date": "2014-01-16 09:30:54.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-3946 ptlrpc: Allow to force crash-dump vs log upon evict",
        "message": "LU-3946 ptlrpc: Allow to force crash-dump vs log upon evict\n\nThis patch is intended to provide a Lustre-Client 2.4.0-RC2 distro\nwith the ability to force LBUG/crash-dump, instead of debug log flush,\nupon eviction. If [obd_]dump_on_eviction = -1 LBUG/crash-dump\n(depending on panic_on_lbug value).\nThis was required as part of LU-3946 debugging where there is a need\nto get a crash-dump to be generated upon eviction in order to\nunderstand the root cause of the problem, and particularly if it is\nrelated to LU-874 and some kind of dead-lock in LDLM, or comes from\nsome tricky issue (scheduling/overload, like in LU-4112).\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=recovery-small\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I1f7ecbdeb9040c69eb0d584b8e6165ed10f892ef\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
